[""],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%86%D9%8E%D9%82%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A8%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to dig, to grave, to bore into (literally, or as to find, or to rummage a territory, etc.)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to teem in holes, to be gappy"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to pierce, to lacerate (the skin)","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to perforate, to drill a hole into (e.g. a wall)","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to drill"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to dig","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to dig into, to investigate thoroughly","tags":["figuratively"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of نَقَبَ (naqaba) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"],"examples":[{"text":"آتُونِي زُبَرَ الْحَدِيدِ حَتَّىٰ إِذَا سَاوَىٰ بَيْنَ الصَّدَفَيْنِ قَالَ ٱنْفُخُوا حَتَّىٰ إِذَا جَعَلَهُ نَارًا قَالَ آتُونِي أُفْرِغْ عَلَيْهِ قِطْرًا ۝ فَمَا ٱسْطَاعُوا أَن يَظْهَرُوهُ وَمَا ٱسْتَطَاعُوا لَهُ نَقْبًا","english":"“Give me bits of iron.” Until he dumped equally high between the two mountain cuttings. He said: “Blow.” Till he made fire. He said: “Bring me molten copper I pour upon it.“ ۝ And they could neither scale nor penetrate it."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"passage, breach, tunnel","examples":[{"text":"لَيْسَ مِنْ بَلَدٍ إِلَّا سَيَطَؤُهُ الدَّجَّالُ إِلَّا مَكَّةَ وَالْمَدِينَةَ وَلَيْسَ نَقْبٌ مِنْ أَنْقَابِهَا إِلَّا عَلَيْهِ الْمَلَائِكَةُ صَافِّينَ تَحْرُسُهَا","english":"There is no land that the False Messiah will not walk on, save for Mecca and Medina. There is no pathway among its pathways that does not have angels in array who watch over it."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of نَقِبَ (naqiba) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to become a leader"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of نِقَاب (niqāb, “veil”)","tags":["form-of","plural"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":null}